<subSubSection id="C36A65251469221123E3FD3D0F6C6B24" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCF36AE1469221123E3FD3D0F6C6B24" blockId="12.[151,1436,581,967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1469221123E3FD3D0F666A94" bold="true" box="[198,326,741,767]" pageId="12" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head rather deep and downward inflected with poorly ossified opercular bones, anterior gill arch with 12–19 developed rakers on lower arm; 7–10 scales in an oblique row between origin of dorsal fin and lateral line.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
